notifications.description:
Configure notifications here. Device Sentinel can send notifications to any phone, tablet, computer, or other device that has a notify service.

There are two notification lists, by priority. High-priority targets will always receive notifications: they bypass Do Not Disturb and quiet hours. Normal-priority targets get standard delivery and are held during quiet hours. Either list may be empty.

Full documentation: {wiki_link}

exclusions.description:
Globally excluded items are never reported, by any part of Device Sentinel, but they are still watched and their habits are learned, so undoing an exclusion is instant and nothing is lost.

The three lists run broad to narrow: integration, label, device. When you exclude at a higher level and save, everything it covers disappears as a choice from the lists below it: exclude an integration and its devices no longer appear and do not need to be removed individually, because the integration already covers them.

Full documentation: {wiki_link}

battery.description:
Every battery Device Sentinel finds is watched by default. A battery is flagged when it is at or below the threshold. Excluding a battery here stops battery reports for that device only; everything else about it stays watched.

The three lists run broad to narrow: integration, label, device. They work like the Global Exclusions lists: exclude at a higher level and save, and everything it covers disappears as a choice from the lists below it.

Full documentation: {wiki_link}
